    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>Topological Sort Visualization</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            margin: 20px;\n        }\n        #graph {\n            margin-top: 20px;\n        }\n        li {\n            list-style-type: none;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>Topological Sort Visualization</h1>\n    <p>In a directed acyclic graph (DAG), a topological sort of vertices is a linear ordering of its vertices such that for every directed edge UV from vertex U to vertex V, U comes before V in the ordering.</p>\n    <input type=\"text\" id=\"edgesInput\" placeholder=\"Enter edges (e.g., A> B, B> C, A> C)\">\n    <button onclick=\"performTopologicalSort()\">Sort</button>\n\n    <h2>Sorted Order:</h2>\n    <ul id=\"output\"></ul>\n\n    <script>\n        function performTopologicalSort() {\n            const input = document.getElementById('edgesInput').value;\n            const edges = input.split(',').map(edge => edge.trim());\n            const graph = {};\n            const inDegree = {};\n\n            edges.forEach(edge => {\n                const [u, v] = edge.split('>').map(node => node.trim());\n                if (!graph[u]) graph[u] = [];\n                graph[u].push(v);\n                inDegree[v] = (inDegree[v] || 0) + 1;\n                if (!inDegree[u]) inDegree[u] = 0; // For nodes that have no incoming edges\n            });\n\n            const zeroInDegreeQueue = [];\n            for (const node in inDegree) {\n                if (inDegree[node] === 0) {\n                    zeroInDegreeQueue.push(node);\n                }\n            }\n\n            const sortedOrder = [];\n            while (zeroInDegreeQueue.length > 0) {\n                const node = zeroInDegreeQueue.shift();\n                sortedOrder.push(node);\n\n                if (graph[node]) {\n                    for (const neighbor of graph[node]) {\n                        inDegree[neighbor]--;\n                        if (inDegree[neighbor] === 0) {\n                            zeroInDegreeQueue.push(neighbor);\n                        }\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n\n            // Check if topological sort is possible (i.e., check for cycles)\n            if (sortedOrder.length !== Object.keys(inDegree).length) {\n                document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = '<li>Graph is cyclic, topological sort not possible.</li>';\n            } else {\n                document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = sortedOrder.map(node => `<li>${node}</li>`).join('');\n            }\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
